          <source>The <ph id="ph1">`break`</ph> statement is frequently used to terminate the processing of a particular case within a <ph id="ph2">`switch`</ph> statement.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Lack of an enclosing iterative or <ph id="ph1">`switch`</ph> statement generates an error.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="109" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Within nested statements, the <ph id="ph1">`break`</ph> statement terminates only the <ph id="ph2">`do`</ph>, <ph id="ph3">`for`</ph>, <ph id="ph4">`switch`</ph>, or <ph id="ph5">`while`</ph> statement that immediately encloses it.</source>
